<br>
It has 100 hps, so be darned sure that your tank has agro solidly before you cast it... one whack from the mob, and it's gone.  Either way, it dies when the mob dies.<br>
<br>
Useless against anything with an AE.  Also, the recast time is waay too long to keep up with a normal group.  Other than that, it has some situational uses. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=skildpade>skildpade</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Conjurer</span><br>  Posts: 219<br> <font color=#333333>(2/28/03 9:46 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerspells.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1866.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_question_mark.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Rage of Zomm</span><hr size=1> I am not sure the hits are that high, i think it is someware in the 80'ish and it doesn't quad, just doubles. When you are using it, it will attack your current target (no target and it suicides at once). It can be used against more than one mob, you just have to issue a new attack command before the current mob is dead. You can use BO and other buffs on it (likely a waste). The use of the pet is situational and in my oppinion almost never usefull. It does however not take a malachite to summon.<br>
